  <brief_title>The Effect of Pullsed Magnetic Field Induction on Improving the Forearm Tissue Muscle Performance</brief_title>
  <official_title>The Effect of Pullsed Magnetic Field Induction on Improving the Forearm Tissue Muscle Performance</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Tel-Aviv Sourasky Medical Center</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Tel-Aviv Sourasky Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pulsed electromagnetic field therapy (PEMFT) is a reparative technique most commonly used in
      the field of orthopedics for the treatment of non-union fractures. The aim is to test the
      effect of the magnetic induction on brute force of treated muscle in oncological patients.
      Oncology patients were chosen as we assume that the ipmrovement will be more noticable in
      oncology patients than in a non-oncology, healthy subjects.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
